<h2>Yahoo! classic </h2>
 <ol>
  <li>Log in to your Yahoo! email account.</li>
  <li>In the upper right-hand corner of the page, locate and click the 'options' link.</li>
  <p>
    <%= image_tag('/images/tutorial/yahoo-classic-step-1.jpg' )%>
  </p>
  <li>Click the 'signature' link in the menu found on the left side of the page.</li>
  <p>
    <%= image_tag('/images/tutorial/yahoo-classic-step-2.jpg' )%>
  </p>

  <li>Make sure that you are in 'Rich Text' mode.  (When you are in 'Rich Text' mode, the link on the right will say 'Plain Text').</li>
  <p>
    <%= image_tag('/images/tutorial/yahoo-classic-step-3.jpg' )%>
  </p>

  <li>  Paste the 'embed text' into th text box. </li>
  <p>
    <%= image_tag('/images/tutorial/yahoo-classic-step-4.jpg' )%>
  </p>

  <li>Make sure that the radio button labeled 'Show a signature on all outgoing messages' is checked, and Click save changes.</li>
  <p>
    <%= image_tag('/images/tutorial/yahoo-classic-step-5.jpg' )%>
  </p>

  <li>That's it. All your email messages will contain your email signature.</li>
  <p>
    <%= image_tag('/images/tutorial/yahoo-step-6.jpg' )%>
  </p>

</ol>
